solution.p:
De acordo com , temos
\frac{\dd z}{\dd t} = \ob{(2xy-3y^4)}{\frac{\partial z}{\partial x}}\ob{(2\cos{2t})}{\frac{\partial x}{\partial t}} 
+ \ob{(x^2+ 12xy^3)}{\frac{\partial z}{\partial y}}\ob{(-\sin{t})}{\frac{\partial y}{\partial t}} 

Note que quando t=0, temos x=\sin{0}=0 e y=\cos{0}=1. Portanto, 


 \left. \frac{\dd z}{\dd t} \right|_{t=0} = (0+3)(2\cos{0})(0+0)(-\sin{0})=6.

assemblage.p:
Suponha que z=f(x, y)  seja uma função diferenciável
    de x e y , onde x = g(s, t) e y= h(s, t) são funções diferenciáveis de s e t.



 \frac{\partial z}{\partial s} = \frac{\partial z}{\partial x}\frac{\partial x}{\partial s}
+ \frac{\partial z}{\partial y}\frac{\partial y}{\partial s}  




  \frac{\partial z}{\partial t} = \frac{\partial z}{\partial x}\frac{\partial x}{\partial t}
+ \frac{\partial z}{\partial y}\frac{\partial y}{\partial t}

solution.p:
De acordo com , temos

        \frac{\partial z}{\partial s} \amp = \ob{(e^x\sin{y})}{\frac{\partial z}{\partial x}}\ob{(t^2)}{\frac{\partial x}{\partial s}} +
         \ob{(e^x\cos{y})}{\frac{\partial x}{\partial s}}\ob{(2st)}{\frac{\partial y}{\partial s}} 


         \amp = t^2e^{st^2}\sin{(s^2t)}+ 2st^{st^2}\cos{(s^2t)} 




        \frac{\partial z}{\partial t} \amp =  \ob{(e^x\sin{y})}{\frac{\partial z}{\partial x}}\ob{(2st)}{\frac{\partial x}{\partial t}} 
        + \ob{(e^x\cos{y})}{\frac{\partial z}{\partial y}}\ob{(s^2)}{\frac{\partial y}{\partial t}}\amp 
         \amp= 2ste^{st^2}\sin{(s^2t)} + s^2e^{st^2}\cos{(s^2t)}
